1
00:01:53,208 --> 00:01:54,333
[MORTE] Hey, wait for me!

2
00:01:54,416 --> 00:01:55,541
Ahhh!

3
00:01:55,625 --> 00:01:57,166
[KYRIE] Ahhh!

4
00:01:59,166 --> 00:02:01,166
[MORTE yelling]

5
00:02:01,250 --> 00:02:02,500
[KYRIE] Morte!

6
00:02:02,583 --> 00:02:04,375
Wasting your energy
yelling won't help anybody,

7
00:02:04,458 --> 00:02:06,333
so try to cool off, okay?

8
00:02:06,416 --> 00:02:08,291
If we don't keep moving
we'll freeze to death

9
00:02:08,375 --> 00:02:10,333
and you're telling
me to cool off?

10
00:02:10,416 --> 00:02:12,916
[TOPPY] I think I
have an idea, kuma!

11
00:02:13,750 --> 00:02:15,791
Hey, did you see
where Toppy went?

12
00:02:15,875 --> 00:02:18,833
No. He's probably
buried under the snow.

13
00:02:18,916 --> 00:02:20,416
[TOPPY] Kyrie,
you're going to have to

14
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:23,125
wear your artificial
ears again...

15
00:02:23,208 --> 00:02:25,333
Then go to the human
village and stir up

16
00:02:25,416 --> 00:02:27,500
trouble with the locals, kuma.

17
00:02:27,583 --> 00:02:30,625
After that, Morte will
show up wearing her

18
00:02:30,708 --> 00:02:33,458
artificial ears and
beat you up, kuma.

19
00:02:33,541 --> 00:02:35,333
Trust me. I know beastmen.

20
00:02:35,416 --> 00:02:37,333
This is the only
way we'll be able...

21
00:02:37,416 --> 00:02:39,041
He's talking
in his sleep again?

22
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:44,750
[MORTE] Okay, Toppy.
Rise and shine!

23
00:02:52,791 --> 00:02:54,166
Kuma?

24
00:02:59,666 --> 00:03:01,208
[KYRIE] So you're
sure this passage leads

25
00:03:01,291 --> 00:03:02,625
to the top of the cliff?

26
00:03:02,708 --> 00:03:04,500
[TOPPY] Even if it doesn't,
it's not as cold in here

27
00:03:04,583 --> 00:03:06,083
as it is outside, kuma.

28
00:03:06,166 --> 00:03:08,375
And I'm not so
sleepy anymore, kuma.

29
00:03:08,458 --> 00:03:10,291
[MORTE] This cave...
It doesn't look like

30
00:03:10,375 --> 00:03:12,500
it was naturally
formed, does it?

31
00:03:14,125 --> 00:03:16,416
It looks like some
kind of ancient ruins.

32
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:18,791
[KYRIE yells]

33
00:03:20,541 --> 00:03:22,750
Aaahhh!

34
00:03:22,833 --> 00:03:24,208
Mummy!

35
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:27,958
What's it doing here?

36
00:03:28,041 --> 00:03:29,875
[MORTE] And why
are there so many?

37
00:03:31,041 --> 00:03:33,041
There aren't any
wounds on them, kuma.

38
00:03:33,125 --> 00:03:36,166
It almost looks like all of them
died of natural causes, kuma.

39
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:38,250
[KYRIE] Great... I guess
that means they all died

40
00:03:38,333 --> 00:03:40,083
after getting trapped in here.

41
00:03:40,166 --> 00:03:41,958
Then we oughta get
moving if we don't wanna

42
00:03:42,041 --> 00:03:44,916
end up the same way. Let's go.

43
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:50,875
♪

44
00:03:53,250 --> 00:03:54,500
[MORTE] What happened?

45
00:03:54,583 --> 00:03:56,541
Is this...?

46
00:03:57,708 --> 00:03:58,541
[KYRIE] Morte?

47
00:03:58,625 --> 00:04:00,000
[TOPPY] What's wrong, kuma?

48
00:04:02,291 --> 00:04:09,625
♪

49
00:04:09,708 --> 00:04:11,208
[MORTE] It is!

50
00:04:12,041 --> 00:04:14,833
[PRIEST] It's time for
you to say goodbye, my dear.

51
00:04:14,916 --> 00:04:17,416
[PAST MORTE] Reve!

52
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:22,125
[PAST MORTE crying]

53
00:04:22,208 --> 00:04:23,583
[MORTE] No...

54
00:04:25,125 --> 00:04:26,500
[MORTE] No!

55
00:04:27,333 --> 00:04:27,958
[KYRIE] Wait!

56
00:04:28,041 --> 00:04:29,083
[TOPPY] You okay, kuma?

57
00:04:29,166 --> 00:04:30,500
[KYRIE] Morte!

58
00:04:37,625 --> 00:04:39,208
I know this place.

59
00:04:41,166 --> 00:04:44,250
[TOPPY] Kyrie?
What's wrong with you? Ah!

60
00:04:47,208 --> 00:04:49,416
What's going on?
How'd I end up

61
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:52,000
back in my home town, kuma?

62
00:05:04,375 --> 00:05:06,875
I knew I recognized this
place. I'd know it anywhere!

63
00:05:06,958 --> 00:05:09,625
It's where I was
working when I met Morte!

64
00:05:09,708 --> 00:05:11,500
I remember seeing this
notice and asking if

65
00:05:11,583 --> 00:05:13,208
I could have a job.

66
00:05:20,166 --> 00:05:21,666
[PAST KYRIE chuckles]

67
00:05:25,833 --> 00:05:27,125
Are you the
owner, sir?

68
00:05:27,208 --> 00:05:29,833
Sorry, kid, but we don't
open for another hour.

69
00:05:29,916 --> 00:05:31,208
Oh, you want the job!

70
00:05:31,291 --> 00:05:32,375
Well, why didn't
you say so?

71
00:05:32,458 --> 00:05:33,750
You have had
experience working in

72
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:35,291
a restaurant
kitchen, haven't you?

73
00:05:35,375 --> 00:05:37,416
Yes! My specialty
is a sand whale dish

74
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:39,625
that'll knock your socks off!

75
00:05:39,708 --> 00:05:41,625
I remember this.
It's exactly what happened

76
00:05:41,708 --> 00:05:44,166
the first day I
got to this town!

77
00:05:44,250 --> 00:05:46,416
How is all of this happening?

78
00:05:49,541 --> 00:05:52,125
[EAGLE MASTER] Where did you
go after you left clock town?

79
00:05:52,208 --> 00:05:53,208
[ALLIGATOR MASTER] Hm?

80
00:05:53,291 --> 00:05:54,750
Have you located
those idiots from the

81
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:56,541
World Destruction Committee?

82
00:05:56,625 --> 00:05:59,291
My mechanical army has
been in constant pursuit,

83
00:05:59,375 --> 00:06:00,958
but I'm afraid
that they recently

84
00:06:01,041 --> 00:06:02,958
lost track of them
on the winter continent,

85
00:06:03,041 --> 00:06:05,000
somewhere in
the Dragon Valley.

86
00:06:05,083 --> 00:06:07,041
And what about
the Destruct Code?

87
00:06:07,125 --> 00:06:08,291
[ALLIGATOR MASTER]
It's still missing,

88
00:06:08,375 --> 00:06:10,875
just like our three
fugitives. But...

89
00:06:10,958 --> 00:06:13,500
is this not an ideal outcome?

90
00:06:13,583 --> 00:06:15,416
Both the Destruct Code
and the members of

91
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,583
the World Destruction
Committee are buried under

92
00:06:17,666 --> 00:06:20,416
several tons of snow
on the winter continent.

93
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:22,208
There is absolutely
no chance they will

94
00:06:22,291 --> 00:06:24,416
escape the Dragon Valley alive.

95
00:06:24,500 --> 00:06:26,625
[EAGLE MASTER] But where
is the meaning in that?

96
00:06:26,708 --> 00:06:28,375
"Meaning"? What difference does

97
00:06:28,458 --> 00:06:30,000
"meaning" make
when your objective

98
00:06:30,083 --> 00:06:31,875
of saving the world is attained?

99
00:06:31,958 --> 00:06:35,416
The Destruct Code is worthless
unless it is in my hands.

100
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:38,333
While I do not intend
to destroy the world...

101
00:06:38,416 --> 00:06:42,416
others must know that I have
the power to do so if I please.

102
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:45,125
Only then will
it be meaningful.

103
00:06:45,208 --> 00:06:46,666
How inane...

104
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:49,875
In that case, go to the Dragon
Valley and find it yourself.

105
00:06:49,958 --> 00:06:51,708
But I suggest you be careful.

106
00:06:51,791 --> 00:06:55,375
You don't want to wander into
the Labyrinth of Memories.

107
00:06:56,208 --> 00:06:57,708
[MORTE] This place...

108
00:06:59,333 --> 00:07:02,625
It's my home... but how?

109
00:07:03,875 --> 00:07:05,125
[WSC SOLDIER] Forgive
me for asking, sir,

110
00:07:05,208 --> 00:07:08,833
but this "Labyrinth of
Memories," what's it like?

111
00:07:08,916 --> 00:07:12,416
Ah. The so-called
"Labyrinth of Memories."

112
00:07:13,083 --> 00:07:14,666
[EAGLE MASTER] Once
someone enters the Labyrinth,

113
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:16,875
there's no way out but death.

114
00:07:16,958 --> 00:07:20,541
They become lost in a dream
world of their own memories...

115
00:07:20,625 --> 00:07:24,583
where they wander hopelessly
until they wither and die.

116
00:07:25,708 --> 00:07:28,458
[PRIEST] His coffin has been
laid to rest inside the temple.

117
00:07:28,541 --> 00:07:30,166
You should go to see him.

118
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:33,666
Which reminds me, I found
this among his things.

119
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:36,083
Can you tell me if
it belonged to him?

120
00:07:37,708 --> 00:07:39,166
[MORTE shaky gasp]

121
00:07:41,125 --> 00:07:43,833
[PRIEST] I see.
Whether or not it was his,

122
00:07:43,916 --> 00:07:46,458
Reve kept it with
him to the very end.

123
00:07:46,541 --> 00:07:49,750
It must have been quite
important to him. Here.

124
00:07:49,833 --> 00:07:52,708
I'm sure he would have
wanted you to have it.

125
00:07:54,833 --> 00:07:56,166
I know this place...

126
00:07:56,250 --> 00:07:58,125
This is where they
brought Reve's coffin.

127
00:07:58,208 --> 00:08:01,458
It's where I first came in
contact with the Destruct Code.

128
00:08:02,250 --> 00:08:04,208
[MORTE gasps]

129
00:08:04,291 --> 00:08:06,500
[MAN] You're Reve's
sister, aren't you?

130
00:08:09,166 --> 00:08:12,708
[MAN] My name is Karna. I'm
a member of the Golden Lions.

131
00:08:13,708 --> 00:08:16,083
[KARNA] Look I'm sorry,
but I have to ask...

132
00:08:16,166 --> 00:08:19,708
Have you ever heard the
stories of the Destruct Code?

133
00:08:19,791 --> 00:08:22,625
I don't even know what that is.

134
00:08:22,708 --> 00:08:24,916
[KARNA] The Destruct Code
is a legendary treasure

135
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:27,958
that's believed to have the
power to destroy the world.

136
00:08:28,041 --> 00:08:29,875
And they say that
the day before he died,

137
00:08:29,958 --> 00:08:32,333
your brother, Reve, told
some guys in his squad

138
00:08:32,416 --> 00:08:34,000
that he'd found it.

139
00:08:36,375 --> 00:08:39,041
If you find anything...
anything unusual in his

140
00:08:39,125 --> 00:08:40,958
possessions and you're
not sure about what it is,

141
00:08:41,041 --> 00:08:43,833
[KARNA] I'd appreciate if
you'd let me know personally.

142
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:51,625
[REVE] Let's rest here.

143
00:08:51,708 --> 00:08:53,125
[PAST MORTE] Seriously?

144
00:08:53,208 --> 00:08:54,583
That must be
embarrassing.

145
00:08:54,666 --> 00:08:56,958
You're supposed to
be the big, tough boy.

146
00:08:57,041 --> 00:08:59,250
Listen, sis...
There's something that

147
00:08:59,333 --> 00:09:01,208
I need to talk
to you about.

148
00:09:01,291 --> 00:09:02,625
What's that?

149
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:04,666
[REVE] It's no big deal, but...
I-I know you're gonna be

150
00:09:04,750 --> 00:09:07,833
against this because you're
my big sister and everything.

151
00:09:07,916 --> 00:09:10,750
But... I just think it's
time for you to know that

152
00:09:10,833 --> 00:09:13,375
I'm going to be joining
the Golden Lions soon.

153
00:09:13,458 --> 00:09:15,041
[gasps]

154
00:09:15,125 --> 00:09:16,875
You don't know what
you're talking about!

155
00:09:16,958 --> 00:09:19,250
Do you have any idea
how dangerous that is?

156
00:09:19,333 --> 00:09:20,916
Well, sometimes
people have to do some

157
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:23,500
dangerous things if they
want to change the world!

158
00:09:23,583 --> 00:09:25,125
Reve...

159
00:09:25,208 --> 00:09:26,750
But why you?

160
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:28,000
Because we
can't let things

161
00:09:28,083 --> 00:09:29,666
go on like
this anymore.

162
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:31,125
I want to help
free all humans

163
00:09:31,208 --> 00:09:32,583
from this beastman
oppression!

164
00:09:32,666 --> 00:09:35,125
[MORTE] No!
Please, Reve, don't!

165
00:09:35,208 --> 00:09:37,583
You don't have to do it!
Please, Reve, stay here!

166
00:09:37,666 --> 00:09:39,458
The world doesn't
have to change!

167
00:09:39,541 --> 00:09:42,250
[MORTE] I'm begging you,
Reve. Stay here with me!

168
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:43,958
Stop him! You've
gotta keep him from

169
00:09:44,041 --> 00:09:46,541
joining the Golden
Lions. You have to!

170
00:09:46,625 --> 00:09:48,083
If you can keep
Reve here with you,

171
00:09:48,166 --> 00:09:50,041
he'll never have to die!

172
00:09:50,125 --> 00:09:53,875
He can live! He can!
You just have to stop him!

173
00:09:53,958 --> 00:09:57,375
[MORTE] Stop him...
Please, stop him...

174
00:09:57,458 --> 00:10:03,000
[crying]

175
00:10:08,333 --> 00:10:09,708
[MORTE] Huh?

176
00:10:17,375 --> 00:10:19,916
[MAN] Nnghhh... Uh.

177
00:10:21,416 --> 00:10:24,000
Dad...? Is that you?

178
00:10:34,625 --> 00:10:36,875
[TOPPY] There are two
kinds of pasts, kuma.

179
00:10:36,958 --> 00:10:38,416
The kind you want to forget,

180
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:40,541
and the kind you
won't ever forget.

181
00:10:40,625 --> 00:10:42,958
[YAPPY] Well, look
what we have here, bear!

182
00:10:44,333 --> 00:10:45,291
[TOPPY] Yappy!

183
00:10:45,375 --> 00:10:47,291
We've been waiting
for you, bear.

184
00:10:47,375 --> 00:10:49,250
[YAPPY] Come on,
let's go, bear!

185
00:10:49,333 --> 00:10:50,583
[TOPPY] Uh, alright.

186
00:10:50,666 --> 00:10:54,583
[cawing]

187
00:10:54,666 --> 00:11:04,666
♪

188
00:11:07,666 --> 00:11:09,083
[giggles]

189
00:11:10,166 --> 00:11:11,541
[MORTE'S DAD] Hm.

190
00:11:11,625 --> 00:11:13,208
[YOUNG MORTE giggles]

191
00:11:16,125 --> 00:11:17,375
[CAFÉ OWNER]
I understand. You've been

192
00:11:17,458 --> 00:11:19,541
moving around a lot lately.

193
00:11:19,625 --> 00:11:22,208
That's perfectly natural
for a boy your age.

194
00:11:22,291 --> 00:11:24,083
You've got to get out there
and experience the world

195
00:11:24,166 --> 00:11:26,583
and all it has to offer while
you still have the chance.

196
00:11:26,666 --> 00:11:28,958
[CAFÉ OWNER] I traveled a
bit myself when I was younger.

197
00:11:29,041 --> 00:11:31,875
So, tell me... where were you
before you ended up here?

198
00:11:31,958 --> 00:11:33,916
[PAST KYRIE] Oh! Well, uh...

199
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:36,625
[CAFÉ OWNER] Oh, nevermind...
Forget I asked.

200
00:11:36,708 --> 00:11:38,708
You don't have to tell
me if you don't want to.

201
00:11:38,791 --> 00:11:40,500
I suppose everybody
has a thing or two

202
00:11:40,583 --> 00:11:42,666
they wouldn't
mind keeping a secret.

203
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,375
What the--?

204
00:11:49,916 --> 00:11:51,458
[KYRIE] Where am I?

205
00:11:51,541 --> 00:12:01,500
♪

206
00:12:03,625 --> 00:12:04,958
[MORTE'S DAD] Aughhh...

207
00:12:05,041 --> 00:12:08,875
Father...! Why do I have
to see all these things again?

208
00:12:08,958 --> 00:12:12,083
[YOUNG MORTE]
Daddy! Please don't go!

209
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,208
Daddy...! Daddy!

210
00:12:17,291 --> 00:12:20,000
[MORTE] Stop this! I don't
want to see any more!

211
00:12:28,708 --> 00:12:31,416
[YOUNG REVE crying]

212
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:34,958
[BOTH sobbing]

213
00:12:35,041 --> 00:12:37,875
[MORTE] No more... no more...

214
00:12:38,666 --> 00:12:41,750
[MORTE] Make it stop!

215
00:12:44,416 --> 00:12:46,750
[YOUNG REVE] Come on, sis!
Dinner's on the table!

216
00:12:48,416 --> 00:12:52,041
[YOUNG REVE] It's your
favorite... sand jellyfish.

217
00:12:53,416 --> 00:12:55,125
[YOUNG REVE] Hurry up, let's go!

218
00:12:55,208 --> 00:12:57,208
Hold on a second. Not so fast!

219
00:12:57,291 --> 00:12:58,875
[MORTE'S DAD] Look
who finally made it!

220
00:12:58,958 --> 00:12:59,916
It's about time!

221
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,708
Your poor Dad's
starving to death!

222
00:13:01,791 --> 00:13:03,916
This is a special
dinner, we finally got some

223
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,125
fish from the Sand Sea.

224
00:13:06,208 --> 00:13:08,500
[MORTE] Mom! Dad!

225
00:13:08,583 --> 00:13:11,375
[MORTE'S MOM] Go ahead...
There's plenty to eat.

226
00:13:11,458 --> 00:13:13,666
Everything looks
great, huh, sis?

227
00:13:13,750 --> 00:13:15,500
[REVE] Let's dig in!

228
00:13:15,583 --> 00:13:17,375
[MORTE] Right. Dig in.

229
00:13:18,416 --> 00:13:19,375
[YOUNG REVE] Here, sis!

230
00:13:19,458 --> 00:13:20,833
Ahhh...!

231
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,250
Delicious!

232
00:13:25,333 --> 00:13:27,208
Well, you don't have to
act so surprised about it.

233
00:13:27,291 --> 00:13:29,500
Your mom's never made a
bad meal in her whole life!

234
00:13:29,583 --> 00:13:34,083
[MORTE'S DAD, MOM,
and YOUNG REVE laugh]

235
00:13:34,166 --> 00:13:35,958
[ALL laugh]

236
00:13:37,291 --> 00:13:38,458
[GOLDEN LION A] Now that
we've got these explosives,

237
00:13:38,541 --> 00:13:41,125
we can finally give the
beastmen a decent fight!

238
00:13:41,208 --> 00:13:44,541
[GOLDEN LION B] Hey,
you over there! Hurry up!

239
00:13:44,625 --> 00:13:47,000
Yeah, yeah. I'm hurrying.

240
00:13:47,083 --> 00:13:48,250
[REVE] Need some help?

241
00:13:48,333 --> 00:13:50,458
No thanks. I've got it.

242
00:13:50,541 --> 00:13:52,541
It may not be easy,
but it's good work.

243
00:13:52,625 --> 00:13:53,791
You wouldn't believe
how much these guys

244
00:13:53,875 --> 00:13:55,250
are paying me for this.

245
00:13:55,333 --> 00:13:56,625
So you're that smuggler?

246
00:13:56,708 --> 00:13:58,333
I've been known to
smuggle a thing or two

247
00:13:58,416 --> 00:13:59,666
if the price is right.

248
00:13:59,750 --> 00:14:01,125
Oh, that's great.

249
00:14:01,208 --> 00:14:02,583
[REVE] Because there's
something I was hoping I could

250
00:14:02,666 --> 00:14:04,250
get you to transport for me.

251
00:14:04,333 --> 00:14:05,875
[AGAN] Hm? What is it?

252
00:14:05,958 --> 00:14:07,625
Weapons? Food?

253
00:14:07,708 --> 00:14:09,250
Just a message.

254
00:14:09,333 --> 00:14:10,500
A message?

255
00:14:10,583 --> 00:14:12,208
[REVE] Yeah, my sister
is living all by herself

256
00:14:12,291 --> 00:14:13,583
back in our village,

257
00:14:13,666 --> 00:14:15,166
and there's something I
need you to tell her for me.

258
00:14:15,250 --> 00:14:19,333
Say... Say that I'm
sorry for making her worry.

259
00:14:19,416 --> 00:14:22,375
Tell her... I promise
I'll make it home safe...

260
00:14:22,458 --> 00:14:24,833
right after I've
changed the world.

261
00:14:24,916 --> 00:14:28,500
And until then...
tell her... to wait for me.

262
00:14:32,208 --> 00:14:34,625
[KYRIE] So it was
Morte's little brother!

263
00:14:34,708 --> 00:14:36,166
[KARNA] Reve,
come here, will ya?

264
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:38,833
'Kay! Thanks
a lot, Mister!

265
00:14:38,916 --> 00:14:40,291
Sure.

266
00:14:43,125 --> 00:14:46,041
[TOPPY] So I looked him square
in the eye and I said to him...

267
00:14:46,125 --> 00:14:47,208
"Maybe you ought
to look at what's

268
00:14:47,291 --> 00:14:49,041
on your head
first, kuma!"

269
00:14:49,125 --> 00:14:50,958
That's right. I don't think
I'm gonna forget the look

270
00:14:51,041 --> 00:14:52,541
that stupid bear
had on his face

271
00:14:52,625 --> 00:14:54,041
for as long as
I live, bear!

272
00:14:54,125 --> 00:14:55,875
[ALL laugh]

273
00:14:55,958 --> 00:14:57,041
So loud!

274
00:14:57,125 --> 00:14:58,000
I know.

275
00:14:58,083 --> 00:15:00,416
[laughing]

276
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:02,083
If you ladies don't
stop looking at me,

277
00:15:02,166 --> 00:15:04,166
you're gonna
make me blush, kuma!

278
00:15:04,250 --> 00:15:05,750
[BOTH] Hmph!

279
00:15:05,833 --> 00:15:08,083
[TOPPY] 'Scuse me, but I
couldn't help noticing you

280
00:15:08,166 --> 00:15:11,000
could use a spoonful
of my sweet honey, kuma.

281
00:15:11,083 --> 00:15:13,000
[GIRL BEAR] Keep
your honey to yourself!

282
00:15:13,083 --> 00:15:15,250
[TOPPY] Kuma!

283
00:15:15,916 --> 00:15:18,166
[TOPPY] Ouch, kuma.

284
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:20,625
Where am I?
What just happened?

285
00:15:20,708 --> 00:15:23,291
And where did that cute
little dwarf bear girl go?

286
00:15:25,416 --> 00:15:27,541
For a dream, that
sure seemed real, kuma...

287
00:15:27,625 --> 00:15:29,000
Oh, no!

288
00:15:31,541 --> 00:15:34,791
[ALLIGATOR MASTER] Why is
the reaction energy so weak?

289
00:15:34,875 --> 00:15:38,041
Is it possible that this is
not the true Destruct Code?

290
00:15:38,125 --> 00:15:40,708
That would certainly
explain things.

291
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:46,458
[GOLDEN LION A] The
beastmen are attacking!

292
00:15:46,541 --> 00:15:48,583
[GOLDEN LION B]
Grab your weapons!

293
00:15:48,666 --> 00:15:52,833
[GOLDEN LIONS yelling]

294
00:15:52,916 --> 00:15:55,333
[GOLDEN LION C] Don't
let them get any closer!

295
00:15:55,416 --> 00:15:56,791
It's him.

296
00:15:58,541 --> 00:15:59,916
Hmmm?

297
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:07,083
♪

298
00:16:07,166 --> 00:16:09,291
[GOLDEN LION B]
Hurry, put out that fire!

299
00:16:10,125 --> 00:16:11,875
[KYRIE] The fire's
reaching the gunpowder!

300
00:16:11,958 --> 00:16:14,291
Get back! You're
not gonna make it!

301
00:16:14,375 --> 00:16:15,958
[KYRIE] Run away!

302
00:16:17,541 --> 00:16:18,916
[ALLIGATOR MASTER grunts]

303
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:23,083
♪

304
00:16:34,041 --> 00:16:35,833
[ALLIGATOR MASTER]
What is this?

305
00:16:39,666 --> 00:16:41,208
[ALLIGATOR MASTER] I see.

306
00:16:50,750 --> 00:16:52,125
[KYRIE] Reve.

307
00:17:01,458 --> 00:17:06,041
[KYRIE'S footsteps]

308
00:17:06,125 --> 00:17:07,500
Ah!

309
00:17:09,208 --> 00:17:11,625
[ALLIGATOR MASTER] So
this little runt...

310
00:17:11,708 --> 00:17:14,041
is the Destruct Code?

311
00:17:14,666 --> 00:17:17,208
[ALLIGATOR MASTER]
Wait. There are two of them?

312
00:17:20,041 --> 00:17:22,000
[ALLIGATOR MASTER]
But... what does this mean?

313
00:17:22,083 --> 00:17:23,750
[TOPPY] Kyrie! Kyrie!

314
00:17:23,833 --> 00:17:24,791
[ALLIGATOR MASTER] Now what?

315
00:17:24,875 --> 00:17:26,291
[TOPPY] You've
gotta wake up, kuma!

316
00:17:27,791 --> 00:17:29,333
[TOPPY] Kyrie!

317
00:17:30,541 --> 00:17:32,208
[KYRIE] Toppy.

318
00:17:35,291 --> 00:17:36,541
Where's Morte's brother?

319
00:17:36,625 --> 00:17:38,458
You were just
having a dream, kuma.

320
00:17:38,541 --> 00:17:39,541
A dream?

321
00:17:39,625 --> 00:17:40,916
We must have
accidentally walked into

322
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:42,791
the Labyrinth
of Memories, kuma.

323
00:17:42,875 --> 00:17:45,041
Labyrinth of
Memories. What is that?

324
00:17:45,125 --> 00:17:47,583
I once heard an old legend
about a mysterious cave

325
00:17:47,666 --> 00:17:49,333
hidden somewhere in
Dragon Valley that

326
00:17:49,416 --> 00:17:51,166
can actually make
people see things that

327
00:17:51,250 --> 00:17:52,708
happened to them
in their past.

328
00:17:52,791 --> 00:17:55,333
I think we may have
found that cave, kuma.

329
00:17:55,416 --> 00:17:57,250
It shows you your past?

330
00:17:57,333 --> 00:17:59,208
All those mummies of
beastmen and humans

331
00:17:59,291 --> 00:18:01,125
[TOPPY] we saw lying
around back there...

332
00:18:01,208 --> 00:18:02,875
they were travelers
who got caught up in their

333
00:18:02,958 --> 00:18:05,416
own memories and
couldn't escape, kuma.

334
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:08,291
So they withered away
and died here, kuma!

335
00:18:08,375 --> 00:18:11,083
[KYRIE] But I've never
been to that place before.

336
00:18:11,166 --> 00:18:14,250
And I've definitely
never met Morte's brother.

337
00:18:17,958 --> 00:18:19,208
Where's Morte?

338
00:18:19,291 --> 00:18:20,541
I haven't seen
her anywhere.

339
00:18:20,625 --> 00:18:22,208
She must be somewhere
else in the cave

340
00:18:22,291 --> 00:18:24,041
reliving her own
memories, kuma!

341
00:18:24,125 --> 00:18:25,625
And if we don't find her
soon, there's gonna be

342
00:18:25,708 --> 00:18:27,708
another mummy
down here, kuma!

343
00:18:27,791 --> 00:18:28,916
[YOUNG MORTE]
And then Reve started

344
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:30,500
stuffing nuts into his mouth.

345
00:18:30,583 --> 00:18:32,458
I told him to slow down,
but he kept eating!

346
00:18:32,541 --> 00:18:35,333
He could barely move
after that, he ate so many!

347
00:18:35,416 --> 00:18:38,583
Oh yeah? Why don't you tell
Mom and Dad how many you ate?

348
00:18:38,666 --> 00:18:41,750
[KYRIE and TOPPY]
Morte! Morte! Morte!

349
00:18:41,833 --> 00:18:43,958
It sounds like somebody's
calling for you, sis.

350
00:18:44,041 --> 00:18:45,125
[TOPPY] Morte!

351
00:18:45,208 --> 00:18:46,791
Don't you think
you should answer them?

352
00:18:46,875 --> 00:18:50,125
[YOUNG MORTE] No...
I just want to stay here.

353
00:18:50,208 --> 00:18:52,500
I don't want to leave here.

354
00:18:52,583 --> 00:18:54,666
I wanna stay here with you!

355
00:18:54,750 --> 00:18:57,416
[KYRIE] Morte!

356
00:18:59,541 --> 00:19:01,458
Ahhh!

357
00:19:01,541 --> 00:19:03,916
[ALLIGATOR MASTER]
The Destruct Code.

358
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:06,375
Those two identical runts...

359
00:19:06,458 --> 00:19:09,125
and the Labyrinth of Memories.

360
00:19:10,375 --> 00:19:11,958
I understand.

361
00:19:12,041 --> 00:19:14,083
So that's what it was.

362
00:19:14,166 --> 00:19:15,541
Found her, kuma!

363
00:19:17,291 --> 00:19:19,208
You've got to pull
yourself together, kuma!

364
00:19:19,291 --> 00:19:20,375
Morte, no!

365
00:19:20,458 --> 00:19:22,000
[TOPPY] Wake up, kuma!

366
00:19:22,083 --> 00:19:23,125
[KYRIE] Morte!

367
00:19:23,208 --> 00:19:24,541
Why won't you leave me alone?

368
00:19:24,625 --> 00:19:26,500
I don't wanna go with you!

369
00:19:26,583 --> 00:19:27,875
It's all right.

370
00:19:27,958 --> 00:19:29,208
You'll be fine.

371
00:19:29,291 --> 00:19:32,041
[rumble]

372
00:19:37,916 --> 00:19:38,833
[MORTE'S DAD] It looks
like it's time for us

373
00:19:38,916 --> 00:19:40,916
to say goodbye, sweetheart.

374
00:19:42,375 --> 00:19:44,666
I won't! I want to
stay here with you!

375
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:46,458
And my mom and my brother!

376
00:19:46,541 --> 00:19:48,500
Don't make me go.

377
00:19:48,583 --> 00:19:49,750
I think you
may have already

378
00:19:49,833 --> 00:19:51,458
figured out
what's happening.

379
00:19:51,541 --> 00:19:53,958
We only exist in
your memories.

380
00:19:54,041 --> 00:19:56,208
I'm sorry, but
none of this is real.

381
00:19:56,291 --> 00:19:58,208
I know it's not!
But the real world

382
00:19:58,291 --> 00:20:00,250
isn't worth saving!
Nobody cares!

383
00:20:00,333 --> 00:20:02,666
Why can't I stay with my
family if it makes me happy?

384
00:20:02,750 --> 00:20:04,708
Why can't I just
stay here with you?

385
00:20:04,791 --> 00:20:05,791
[KYRIE] Morte!

386
00:20:05,875 --> 00:20:07,291
[TOPPY] Morte!

387
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:10,666
This is bad!

388
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:12,125
Whoa, are
you okay, kuma?

389
00:20:12,208 --> 00:20:13,416
Yeah.

390
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:15,250
Let's get out of here!
There isn't much time, kuma!

391
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:16,583
Can't you hear
your friends trying

392
00:20:16,666 --> 00:20:18,583
desperately to save
your life, Morte?

393
00:20:18,666 --> 00:20:21,458
[KYRIE and TOPPY
heavy breathing]

394
00:20:21,541 --> 00:20:23,375
[MORTE'S DAD] In your travels
with them, I'm sure you

395
00:20:23,458 --> 00:20:25,375
came across lots
of different people,

396
00:20:25,458 --> 00:20:28,500
some of them struggling
just to stay alive.

397
00:20:28,583 --> 00:20:31,125
The real world
is their world too.

398
00:20:31,208 --> 00:20:32,583
And I don't think
they're the only ones

399
00:20:32,666 --> 00:20:34,125
who think it's worth saving.

400
00:20:34,208 --> 00:20:35,250
We're going to
be crushed before

401
00:20:35,333 --> 00:20:38,125
she even wakes up! Hurry!

402
00:20:38,875 --> 00:20:40,041
[KYRIE and TOPPY scream]

403
00:20:40,125 --> 00:20:41,958
[MORTE'S DAD] The world
is constantly changing.

404
00:20:42,041 --> 00:20:43,916
If things are bad right
now, it just takes time

405
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:45,750
and work to change
fix them, right?

406
00:20:45,833 --> 00:20:47,458
As long as there
are people like them.

407
00:20:47,541 --> 00:20:49,666
The cave's collapsing.
Don't stop, kuma!

408
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:52,416
What makes you think
that I'd want to stop?!

409
00:20:53,708 --> 00:20:55,000
[MORTE'S DAD] Or even us.

410
00:20:55,083 --> 00:20:56,250
You could say
your mother and I

411
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:59,041
have changed the world
in a very important way.

412
00:20:59,125 --> 00:21:01,583
[MORTE'S DAD] The proof
is right in front of me.

413
00:21:01,666 --> 00:21:03,458
Huh?

414
00:21:03,541 --> 00:21:05,250
[BOTH chuckle]

415
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:07,750
You're the proof, Morte.

416
00:21:09,458 --> 00:21:10,625
I am?

417
00:21:10,708 --> 00:21:12,166
That's right.

418
00:21:12,250 --> 00:21:15,000
[MORTE'S DAD] Now it's your
turn to try to change the world.

419
00:21:15,083 --> 00:21:16,875
And you will.

420
00:21:16,958 --> 00:21:19,583
[MORTE'S MOM] We want you
to live your real life, Morte.

421
00:21:19,666 --> 00:21:21,333
Please, for us.

422
00:21:21,416 --> 00:21:23,750
[MORTE'S DAD] Go create
a new future, sweetheart.

423
00:21:23,833 --> 00:21:26,791
One where everybody
in the world can be happy.

424
00:21:26,875 --> 00:21:28,708
[shaky gasp]

425
00:21:28,791 --> 00:21:31,375
[MORTE] Dad, Mom! Wait!

426
00:21:32,375 --> 00:21:35,833
[REVE] I'm sorry I didn't
keep my promise, sis.

427
00:21:35,916 --> 00:21:37,333
But I feel a whole
lot better knowing

428
00:21:37,416 --> 00:21:39,125
you're not alone anymore.

429
00:21:39,208 --> 00:21:41,291
I'm so happy that
you're doing okay.

430
00:21:41,375 --> 00:21:44,291
Reve, wait! Mom... Dad...

431
00:21:44,375 --> 00:21:46,666
Please, don't leave me!

432
00:21:49,083 --> 00:21:50,541
[TOPPY] Move, kuma!

433
00:21:56,625 --> 00:21:57,791
[grunts]

434
00:21:57,875 --> 00:21:59,375
We're safe, kuma.

435
00:21:59,458 --> 00:22:00,750
[KYRIE and TOPPY] Huh?

436
00:22:00,833 --> 00:22:02,250
[KYRIE] We're outside!

437
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,083
Morte! You're
finally awake, kuma!

438
00:22:07,166 --> 00:22:08,750
I'm glad you made it.

439
00:22:08,833 --> 00:22:11,625
Kyrie... Toppy...

440
00:22:13,583 --> 00:22:15,500
[EAGLE MASTER]
We've found you at last.

441
00:22:15,583 --> 00:22:18,041
You World Destruction
Committee scoundrels.

442
00:22:18,125 --> 00:22:20,416
Now then... give
me the Destruct Code

443
00:22:20,500 --> 00:22:22,500
and I might let you live!

444
00:22:22,583 --> 00:22:29,708
♪

445
00:24:03,333 --> 00:24:05,291
[MORTE] My family
is never coming back.

446
00:24:05,375 --> 00:24:06,625
[TOPPY] That cute
dwarf bear girl isn't

447
00:24:06,708 --> 00:24:08,291
coming back either, kuma.

448
00:24:08,375 --> 00:24:10,625
[KYRIE] The past
doesn't ever come back.

449
00:24:10,708 --> 00:24:12,833
The Destruct Code
will be deciphered.

450
00:24:12,916 --> 00:24:15,333
The world we live
in is falling apart.

451
00:24:15,416 --> 00:24:17,500
What fate awaits us now?

452
00:24:17,583 --> 00:24:20,083
Next time on
Sands of Destruction,

453
00:24:20,166 --> 00:24:22,208
"There Are Two
Kinds of Futures."

454
00:24:22,291 --> 00:24:23,833
[MORTE] Will it be destruction?

455
00:24:23,916 --> 00:24:25,208
[KYRIE] Will it be salvation?

456
00:24:25,291 --> 00:24:26,666
[TOPPY] Will it be a bear?

457
00:24:26,750 --> 00:24:28,750
[MORTE] That would be
three futures, not two.

458
00:24:28,833 --> 00:24:30,208
[TOPPY] Kuma.

